00:19:44,735 --> 00:19:46,626
out of the blue,

512
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:49,213
skip meals, take meal
replacement bars to school.

513
00:19:49,298 --> 00:19:50,471
As a nine‐year‐old?

514
00:19:50,556 --> 00:19:52,339
Mm‐hmm.

515
00:19:52,876 --> 00:19:54,548
Yeah, and...

516
00:19:55,353 --> 00:19:58,634
he would make me
take my shirt off

517
00:19:59,009 --> 00:20:01,071
so he could take pictures
of my body

518
00:20:01,376 --> 00:20:04,681
to, um, put up on the wall
in the basement

519
00:20:04,767 --> 00:20:07,525
next to the makeshift gym
that he'd built for me

520
00:20:07,617 --> 00:20:09,274
to track my process.

521
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:12,067
There was
a body progress chart.

522
00:20:12,688 --> 00:20:14,165
And if I would ever walk by him,

523
00:20:14,290 --> 00:20:16,166
he would smack my gut and say,

524
00:20:16,251 --> 00:20:17,744
"Jesus, look at that thing."

525
00:20:17,837 --> 00:20:19,082
[somber music]

526
00:20:19,469 --> 00:20:21,410
"Got a lot of work left to do,
don't we, buddy?"

527
00:20:22,173 --> 00:20:23,913
And what's worse is,

528
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:27,212
if I ever had a good weigh‐in,
which was not very often,

529
00:20:27,649 --> 00:20:30,635
I, uh, I would be over the moon

530
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,430
because it would make me
feel loved.

531
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:36,550
♪ ♪

532
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,664
[sighs]

533
00:20:39,282 --> 00:20:42,431
Then... this one time,

534
00:20:42,921 --> 00:20:44,823
I guess I would've been
in middle school by this point,

535
00:20:44,907 --> 00:20:46,560
I just... I...

536
00:20:46,914 --> 00:20:49,188
I hated everything
about myself.

537
00:20:50,782 --> 00:20:52,441
So I tried to hang myself.

538
00:20:52,985 --> 00:20:54,276
What?

539
00:20:54,797 --> 00:20:56,453
Jesus, Iggy.

540
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:58,360
- No, it's okay.
- [cries]

541
00:20:58,758 --> 00:21:00,891
It didn't work, obviously.

542
00:21:02,046 --> 00:21:03,931
Ironically, I was too fat

543
00:21:04,016 --> 00:21:05,595
for the rod
in the basement closet

544
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:08,603
to hold me up,
and it crashed down on my head,

545
00:21:08,688 --> 00:21:11,337
and my mom heard the sound
and came to help me.

546
00:21:11,422 --> 00:21:14,228
- What?
- What did your dad say?

547
00:21:14,313 --> 00:21:15,422
Oh.

548
00:21:15,977 --> 00:21:18,861
My dad, um, well,

549
00:21:18,946 --> 00:21:20,189
that night at my weigh‐in,

550
00:21:20,274 --> 00:21:22,688
he just snapped
another polaroid for the wall

551
00:21:22,914 --> 00:21:24,731
and acted like nothing
ever happened.

552
00:21:25,956 --> 00:21:27,332
[scoffs]

553
00:21:27,758 --> 00:21:29,352
That's my dad for you.

554
00:21:34,676 --> 00:21:36,219
[sighs]

555
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:39,779
These are his words,

556
00:21:40,136 --> 00:21:42,134
but they don't control me
anymore.

557
00:21:42,219 --> 00:21:43,267
They do not.

558
00:21:43,352 --> 00:21:45,073
They serve as a reminder
of all of the things

559
00:21:45,157 --> 00:21:46,996
that I have conquered,
which is a lot,

560
00:21:47,516 --> 00:21:49,290
and sometimes
I look at these words,

561
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:52,431
and they remind that
I'm not that kid anymore

562
00:21:52,516 --> 00:21:53,901
and that I'm making
better decisions.

563
00:21:53,985 --> 00:21:56,214
I'm making healthy decisions
in my life.

564
00:21:59,133 --> 00:22:02,511
And that I no longer need to
stand around with my shirt off

565
00:22:03,016 --> 00:22:05,610
- and let others judge me.
- What?

566
00:22:07,555 --> 00:22:09,501
You know that's not
what I was doing, right?

567
00:22:09,586 --> 00:22:10,769
I'm fine.

568
00:22:11,547 --> 00:22:13,126
I am more than fine.

569
00:22:13,218 --> 00:22:14,999
You can rest easy.

570
00:22:15,227 --> 00:22:18,313
Now if you'll excuse me,
I have patients to see.

571
00:22:18,966 --> 00:22:20,092
[door clicks open]

572
00:22:20,382 --> 00:22:23,126
No, I'm... I'm being careful.

573
00:22:23,211 --> 00:22:24,783
Yeah.

574
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:27,516
Ma, I'm gonna see you soon.

575
00:22:27,961 --> 00:22:30,399
Okay, yeah.
I love you too.

576
00:22:30,586 --> 00:22:31,874
All right.

577
00:22:32,313 --> 00:22:34,672
Heard you pulled off
one hell of a TAVR.

578
00:22:34,821 --> 00:22:36,743
Just this side of genius.

579
00:22:36,828 --> 00:22:38,423
I accept your apology, Max.

580
00:22:38,508 --> 00:22:39,737
You need anything else
while you're here?

581
00:22:39,821 --> 00:22:41,595
Aw, no, just catching up
with some folks.

582
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,220
You know, I missed my favorite
scrub nurse in OR today, JJ.

583
00:22:44,305 --> 00:22:45,102
- Devlin.
- Yeah.

584
00:22:45,187 --> 00:22:46,941
He passed away
a few months ago.

585
00:22:47,026 --> 00:22:48,403
COVID.

586
00:22:49,436 --> 00:22:51,103
[sighs] That's too bad.

587
00:22:51,188 --> 00:22:52,618
Everything's changed.

588
00:22:52,703 --> 00:22:54,462
- Dr. Max Goodwin.
- That's me.

589
00:22:54,547 --> 00:22:56,649
- You're under arrest.
- Whoa, what's going on?

590
00:22:56,733 --> 00:22:57,633
For what?

591
00:22:57,718 --> 00:22:59,618
For writing
700 Oxycodone prescriptions,

592
00:22:59,703 --> 00:23:01,306
each one over 100 milligrams,

593
00:23:01,391 --> 00:23:03,227
and distributing them
with bike messengers.

594
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:04,531
Oh, that.

595
00:23:04,615 --> 00:23:06,575
It's nice to see some things
haven't changed.

596
00:23:06,659 --> 00:23:09,245
[beeper beeping]

597
00:23:09,329 --> 00:23:12,860
[fast‐paced dramatic music]

598
00:23:12,985 --> 00:23:14,540
BP's 80/40 and falling.

599
00:23:14,625 --> 00:23:15,743
Push epi, I'm coming in.

600
00:23:15,828 --> 00:23:17,253
I need an echo over here.

601
00:23:17,337 --> 00:23:18,641
What happened?

602
00:23:18,758 --> 00:23:21,422
- The clip didn't hold.
- His heart is failing.

603
00:23:21,507 --> 00:23:26,137
♪ ♪

604
00:23:27,095 --> 00:23:28,262
[sighs]

605
00:23:28,346 --> 00:23:31,641
[fast‐paced percussive music]

606
00:23:32,955 --> 00:23:34,205
The DA only agreed

607
00:23:34,290 --> 00:23:36,250
to not press charges
for narcotics trafficking

608
00:23:36,334 --> 00:23:38,040
because
you're an essential worker.

609
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:39,754
- Huh.
- Congratulations.

610
00:23:39,838 --> 00:23:41,756
You're one of the select few
to benefit from COVID‐19.

611
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:42,946
Thanks for getting me out.

612
00:23:43,031 --> 00:23:44,454
I have half a mind
to leave you in there.

613
00:23:44,538 --> 00:23:46,469
You know, pharmacies
mail opioids all the time.

614
00:23:46,554 --> 00:23:49,014
Bike messengers
are almost the same.

615
00:23:49,159 --> 00:23:51,203
I wonder if you've ever
considered how exhausting it is

616
00:23:51,287 --> 00:23:52,735
to be your boss.

617
00:23:53,141 --> 00:23:54,570
All your wonderful ideas

618
00:23:54,686 --> 00:23:55,915
that come with such chaos,

619
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,396
every single one.

620
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,731
[sighs]
It's funny.

621
00:23:58,815 --> 00:24:01,609
The thing you're best at is the
part of my job I hate the most.

622
00:24:01,693 --> 00:24:03,569
- You ignore reality.
- That's not fair.

623
00:24:03,653 --> 00:24:06,656
Says the man who just
sent 70,000 milligrams of Oxy

624
00:24:06,740 --> 00:24:08,157
out into the street
via bike messenger.

625
00:24:08,241 --> 00:24:10,076
I know it seems
like a good idea.

626
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,899
Hell, it might even be
a good idea,

627
00:24:12,116 --> 00:24:14,535
but it's my job to deal
with the reality of your ideas,

628
00:24:14,682 --> 00:24:17,142
in this case criminal reality.
Optics matter.

629
00:24:17,375 --> 00:24:18,867
Patients matter.

630
00:24:19,297 --> 00:24:22,024
I'm glad you're
helping people, Max, truly.

631
00:24:22,213 --> 00:24:24,633
But your plan
has no accountability.

632
00:24:24,821 --> 00:24:26,300
You don't know where
these drugs are going.

633
00:24:26,384 --> 00:24:27,492
You just don't.

634
00:24:27,577 --> 00:24:30,538
And opioids,
the potential for abuse,

635
00:24:30,847 --> 00:24:32,774
it's a very emotional issue.

636
00:24:33,475 --> 00:24:36,016
To many people,
opioids aren't pain medicine.

637
00:24:36,101 --> 00:24:38,019
They're what killed
someone they loved.

638
00:24:38,354 --> 00:24:41,273
[somber music]

639
00:24:41,357 --> 00:24:42,984
♪ ♪

640
00:24:43,068 --> 00:24:44,861
[sighs]

641
00:24:45,643 --> 00:24:47,438
- Wait.
- Iggy.

642
00:24:47,758 --> 00:24:49,313
Iggy, I wasn't judging you.

643
00:24:49,398 --> 00:24:50,648
You could've fooled me.

644
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:53,402
It was just... people die
from what you're doing.

645
00:24:53,703 --> 00:24:54,954
- What did she say?
- [chatter]

646
00:24:55,038 --> 00:24:56,622
[murmuring continues]

647
00:24:57,195 --> 00:25:00,909
[dramatic music]

648
00:25:01,002 --> 00:25:04,089
In here.
In here.

649
00:25:09,419 --> 00:25:11,087
- Ig.
- [sighs]

650
00:25:11,179 --> 00:25:13,133
Ig, look, I'm sorry
for making a scene.

651
00:25:13,279 --> 00:25:14,739
You should be.

652
00:25:15,281 --> 00:25:16,570
It's just

653
00:25:16,655 --> 00:25:19,853
I've seen people in my ED
with eating disorders.

654
00:25:19,938 --> 00:25:21,814
I mean, I've known people
with eating disorders.

655
00:25:21,898 --> 00:25:23,352
- [sighs]
- Some of them...

656
00:25:23,437 --> 00:25:24,691
they're not here anymore.

657
00:25:24,776 --> 00:25:27,307
- Mm‐hmm.
- Look.

658
00:25:27,711 --> 00:25:30,129
I know as well anyone

659
00:25:30,214 --> 00:25:32,758
that the truth
is really difficult.

660
00:25:32,912 --> 00:25:35,998
I'm sorry.
What are you doing?

661
00:25:36,238 --> 00:25:38,698
Are you comparing your issues
to mine right now?

662
00:25:38,963 --> 00:25:40,374
Let me just mirror
that back for you

663
00:25:40,458 --> 00:25:41,834
so you can hear it out loud.

664
00:25:41,918 --> 00:25:43,870
I'm on the Jimmy Kimmel diet,

665
00:25:44,276 --> 00:25:47,237
and you almost killed a patient
because you are a drug addict.

666
00:25:48,994 --> 00:25:51,838
- Not the same.
- That was way out of line.

667
00:25:51,928 --> 00:25:53,784
- I'm outta line?
- It's not hard, Lauren.

668
00:25:53,869 --> 00:25:55,034
This is a hospital.

669
00:25:55,119 --> 00:25:56,704
There's only one line
that matters.

670
00:25:56,842 --> 00:25:59,432
You were hurting patients.
I am not.

671
00:25:59,541 --> 00:26:00,917
Plain and simple!

672
00:26:01,056 --> 00:26:02,849
Patients aren't
the only people you can hurt.

673
00:26:02,934 --> 00:26:04,518
- Oh, yeah?
- Well, I think the janitors

674
00:26:04,603 --> 00:26:05,904
- are safe from my eating too.
- Yeah?

675
00:26:05,988 --> 00:26:07,260
What about your kids?

676
00:26:09,237 --> 00:26:11,332
- Excuse me?
- You're starving yourself.

677
00:26:11,417 --> 00:26:12,782
You think
they don't notice that?

678
00:26:12,867 --> 00:26:13,993
- You stop talking.
- How many meals have you

679
00:26:14,077 --> 00:26:15,325
had with them
where you haven't eaten anything?

680
00:26:15,409 --> 00:26:16,707
- Stop.
- How many have you skipped altogether?

681
00:26:16,791 --> 00:26:18,042
I mean, what kind
of screwed up issues

682
00:26:18,126 --> 00:26:19,942
are your kids gonna have
with food because of you?

683
00:26:20,026 --> 00:26:21,595
[knocking]
Occupied!

684
00:26:24,218 --> 00:26:26,094
It's a bad time, Gladys.

685
00:26:26,179 --> 00:26:28,264
It's Dr. Kapoor.

686
00:26:28,526 --> 00:26:29,819
The clip failed,

687
00:26:29,904 --> 00:26:31,822
tore right through
the valve leaflets.

688
00:26:31,907 --> 00:26:32,992
I'm gonna have to crack open
his chest

689
00:26:33,076 --> 00:26:34,451
and put in an artificial valve.

690
00:26:34,536 --> 00:26:36,287
That's a big surgery.

691
00:26:36,437 --> 00:26:38,026
I thought you said you
couldn't sew into the muscle.

692
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:41,009
- What changed?
- Nothing. Not a damn thing.

693
00:26:41,263 --> 00:26:43,283
But he'll make it through
the surgery, right?

694
00:26:43,507 --> 00:26:46,426
[somber music]

695
00:26:47,174 --> 00:26:49,425
♪ ♪

696
00:26:49,836 --> 00:26:51,112
That's why I thought
you should see him now,

697
00:26:51,196 --> 00:26:52,970
and have one more moment
with him

698
00:26:54,284 --> 00:26:55,556
in case...

699
00:26:56,184 --> 00:26:57,644
I'm gonna go prep.

700
00:26:57,729 --> 00:27:04,861
♪ ♪

701
00:27:05,687 --> 00:27:07,197
[grunts]

702
00:27:07,845 --> 00:27:09,209
[sighs]

703
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:11,377
You're fully effaced
and dilated,

704
00:27:11,462 --> 00:27:13,244
but the baby's still
at minus three position.

705
00:27:13,329 --> 00:27:15,455
Ella, the delivery isn't
progressing as I had hoped.

706
00:27:15,540 --> 00:27:16,517
What does that mean?

707
00:27:16,602 --> 00:27:19,580
When your contraction comes,
you need to push real hard.

708
00:27:19,665 --> 00:27:21,541
Oh, my God,
this is a disaster.

709
00:27:21,626 --> 00:27:22,978
Maybe you could
hold her hand.

710
00:27:24,606 --> 00:27:26,953
- [heavy breathing]
- E‐Ella.

711
00:27:27,038 --> 00:27:28,047
Look.
Look.

712
00:27:28,132 --> 00:27:29,781
Count them out with me, okay?

713
00:27:29,866 --> 00:27:31,492
- [groans]
- Here we go.

714
00:27:31,688 --> 00:27:33,531
Give me
the biggest push you got.

715
00:27:33,616 --> 00:27:35,304
- You can do this.
- Come on, come on.

716
00:27:35,389 --> 00:27:38,328
- No, I can't!
- Stop, I don't want to!

717
00:27:38,413 --> 00:27:41,547
What if the baby's not okay?
What if I hurt it?

718
00:27:42,123 --> 00:27:44,398
What I ate undercooked meat
and didn't know it?

719
00:27:44,483 --> 00:27:46,054
And seven weeks ago
I took a bath

720
00:27:46,139 --> 00:27:47,305
right after the tub was cleaned,

721
00:27:47,389 --> 00:27:48,515
and the water
probably had bleach in it.

722
00:27:48,599 --> 00:27:50,023
What kind of mom
is that careless?

723
00:27:50,108 --> 00:27:51,275
You are not careless.

724
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,828
You have disorder that sends
your pregnancy into overdrive,

725
00:27:53,913 --> 00:27:56,165
but you fought it,
and you've made it this far.

726
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:58,501
I cheated.
I got scans all the time.

727
00:27:58,586 --> 00:27:59,703
Sometimes two days in a row

728
00:27:59,788 --> 00:28:01,621
in case something happened
while I was sleeping.

729
00:28:01,705 --> 00:28:03,070
But then everything shut down,

730
00:28:03,155 --> 00:28:04,735
and Vijay got sick,
and I don't know why,

731
00:28:04,819 --> 00:28:06,570
but I just convinced myself

732
00:28:06,655 --> 00:28:09,496
that the baby was going to be
okay as long as he was okay.

733
00:28:09,581 --> 00:28:10,832
What if Vijay's not okay?

734
00:28:10,917 --> 00:28:13,002
Ella!
Everything on that monitor

735
00:28:13,087 --> 00:28:14,630
says that your baby
is going to be okay,

736
00:28:14,714 --> 00:28:15,774
but you have to deliver it...

737
00:28:15,858 --> 00:28:17,492
- No!
- Oh.

738
00:28:17,577 --> 00:28:19,000
- Contractions peaking.
- Aah!

739
00:28:19,085 --> 00:28:21,523
You can do it.
Your baby needs you to push now.

740
00:28:21,608 --> 00:28:24,403
[grunts] Aah.

741
00:28:25,673 --> 00:28:27,195
[crying]

742
00:28:30,443 --> 00:28:33,362
[crying]

743
00:28:40,741 --> 00:28:42,203
Eh?

744
00:28:42,846 --> 00:28:45,181
- Yeah, yeah, buddy?
- What is it?

745
00:28:46,567 --> 00:28:48,152
Hit me.

746
00:28:48,831 --> 00:28:50,789
You're such a good dad.

747
00:28:51,574 --> 00:28:53,117
- Aw, I don't know.
- I...

748
00:28:59,871 --> 00:29:02,343
If this doesn't work out...

749
00:29:04,987 --> 00:29:06,726
Will you look after

750
00:29:07,550 --> 00:29:09,461
Ella and the baby?

751
00:29:12,682 --> 00:29:14,226
[crying]

752
00:29:44,706 --> 00:29:46,304
You've got this.

753
00:29:46,693 --> 00:29:48,203
You can do it.

754
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:51,367
Hey.

755
00:29:51,615 --> 00:29:52,866
And I am dying...

756
00:29:53,137 --> 00:29:54,513
- What are you talking about?
- Don't be silly.

757
00:29:54,597 --> 00:29:55,890
You are going to be annoying her

758
00:29:55,975 --> 00:29:57,601
for the rest of your life, okay?

759
00:29:59,304 --> 00:30:00,726
Please.

760
00:30:04,107 --> 00:30:06,390
If something happens, I...

761
00:30:07,980 --> 00:30:09,929
[cries]
Yes.

762
00:30:10,014 --> 00:30:11,257
Obviously.

763
00:30:13,482 --> 00:30:14,441
Good.

764
00:30:14,526 --> 00:30:16,320
[sighs]

765
00:30:27,622 --> 00:30:30,492
[somber music]

766
00:30:30,820 --> 00:30:32,437
Listen, Iggy.

767
00:30:32,828 --> 00:30:34,795
- Lauren, I'm fine.
- No.

768
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,258
I never should've dragged
your kids into this.

769
00:30:38,904 --> 00:30:40,429
I'm really sorry.

770
